# Planner Portfolio - exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit / run-002

## Preserved Context

- Run `001` completed its ordered job rather than failing. The finished chain
  froze the mission object set and handed off explicit downstream tests.
- Step `006` promotes exactly two frozen objects on the canonical one-bridge
  packet ledger:
  repaired `Template-Defect Near-Closure`
  and repaired `Windowed Spectator-Leakage Budget`.
- The theorem-facing carried family is
  `F_SL(rho)` for `0 < rho <= 1/16`,
  with
  `F_SL(1/16)`
  as the recorded boundary-friendly witness for
  `G_tmpl(P_n; I) = (Delta_tmpl, Delta_spec)`.
- The obstruction-facing carried friendly stress set is
  `{F_SS(1/12), F_SL(1/16)}`,
  with repaired leakage sheet
  `G_leak(P_n; I) = (L_tot, L_mirror, L_companion, L_feedback, L_cross)`.
- `F_SS(mu)` remains the strongest positive witness on disk:
  it is still the only recorded pro-circuit family that passed all three
  Step-4 candidates on one explicit exact sheet.
- `F_DT(delta, eta)` remains the hostile anti-family, but the repo still owes
  at least one exact same-currency hostile ledger for some downstream theorem
  claims.
- No implication or equivalence between
  `G_tmpl`
  and
  `G_leak`
  has yet been earned. Replanning should treat them as distinct promoted
  objects unless a new chain proves otherwise.

## Portfolio Summary

### Chain 01 - Family-Level Template-Defect Theorem On `F_SL(rho)`

Central premise: the cleanest next theorem object is to turn the Step-6
handoff for
`Template-Defect Near-Closure`
into one exact family theorem on the carried scale-separated family
`F_SL(rho)`,
including the extremal boundary question at
`rho = 1/16`.

### Chain 02 - Classwise Leakage Sharpness And Friendly-Minimality Theorem

Central premise: the strongest obstruction-facing object is the repaired
classwise leakage sheet itself. The next honest theorem is to prove the exact
friendly sharpness and minimality of that sheet on
`{F_SS(1/12), F_SL(1/16)}`,
then pin as much hostile overload as the same exact currency actually supports.

### Chain 03 - Joint Feasibility Frontier On The Canonical One-Bridge Class

Central premise: the main strategic uncertainty is now the intersection of the
two promoted gates, not their definitions. Treat
`G_tmpl`
as the Tao-shape screen and
`G_leak`
as the isolation screen, parameterize the full frozen one-bridge packet class,
and map the exact joint feasibility frontier.

### Chain 04 - Moonshot Near-Circuit Promotion From `F_SS`

Central premise: the portfolio still needs a genuine kill route for the
firewall idea. Start from the strongest recorded positive witness
`F_SS`,
upgrade it from a dossier pass to an exact reduced dynamical test, and allow
one minimal exact extension only if the frozen witness nearly works honestly.

## Major Differences Between Chains

- Chain 01 is theorem-facing and family-local. It tries to close one exact
  formula problem on
  `F_SL(rho)`
  for
  `G_tmpl`,
  not a general one-bridge frontier or a counterexample build.
- Chain 02 is classwise obstruction work. It is about spectator budgets and
  sharpness on the repaired leakage sheet, not role-template fit.
- Chain 03 is the structured follow-on that keeps both promoted objects with
  non-overlapping roles. It studies the joint admissible region on the whole
  frozen one-bridge class rather than one witness family.
- Chain 04 is constructive and adversarial. It tries to beat the obstruction by
  producing an explicit exact near-circuit candidate, not by proving a theorem
  first.

## Portfolio Discipline

- Start from the Step-6 frozen packet sheet, window `I = [0, 1]`, thresholds,
  sign sheets, and no-overclaim limits. Do not reopen the completed
  definition-freeze chain unless a live branch hits its own kill condition.
- Keep theorem claims inside the audited packet class and fixed interaction
  currency unless a chain explicitly earns a larger exact class.
- Treat useful negative results as first-class outputs:
  corrected threshold sheet,
  exact family-local failure,
  gate separation,
  or constructive failure atlas.
- Keep one moonshot branch in the top portfolio. This mission is supposed to
  test whether the Atlas mechanism insight can become a real theorem or a real
  counterexample, not just a cleaner audit memo.

## Suggested Priority

- First priority: Chain 03.
  It is the best structured follow-on after Step 6 because it uses both
  promoted objects exactly as frozen and can decide whether the next decisive
  result is a one-bridge impossibility theorem, a narrow survivor packet, or a
  proof that the two gates really stay split.
- Second priority: Chain 01.
  It is the cleanest single-object theorem route and has the most direct path
  to a proposition-shaped result from the current record.
- Third priority: Chain 02.
  It has the strongest obstruction floor, but it still depends on pinning the
  hostile same-currency ledger carefully enough to avoid fake overload claims.
- Keep Chain 04 in the active portfolio despite its lower floor.
  It has the highest mission-level upside because an explicit exact near-circuit
  would kill the firewall idea cleanly.

